1
00:00:36,467 --> 00:00:38,100
<i> That's Miss Andrea!</i>

2
00:00:38,233 --> 00:00:39,400
<i> Help!</i>

3
00:00:40,933 --> 00:00:42,633
<i> Dad!</i>

4
00:00:42,767 --> 00:00:43,600
<i> Manuel!</i>

5
00:00:43,733 --> 00:00:44,500
<i> Manuel!</i>

6
00:00:44,633 --> 00:00:46,167
<i>Stay away,
and keep your kids back.</i>

7
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:48,867
<i>For now, stop claiming Manuel
as yours.</i>

8
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,267
<i> Ma'am, I'm really sorry,</i>

9
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:53,533
<i>but only immediate family
allowed here.</i>

10
00:00:53,667 --> 00:00:54,967
<i> He's bleeding into the airway.</i>

11
00:00:55,100 --> 00:00:56,533
<i> Go to the ER now!</i>

12
00:00:56,667 --> 00:00:57,933
<i>- Manuel.
- Dad?</i>

13
00:00:58,067 --> 00:00:59,200
<i>- Stay away!
- Dad!</i>

14
00:00:59,333 --> 00:01:00,533
<i> Stay away!</i>

15
00:01:00,667 --> 00:01:04,533
<i>If Dad dies, Mom, I won't
be able to forgive myself.</i>

16
00:01:04,667 --> 00:01:06,767
<i> Mom, please forgive me.</i>

17
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:09,100
<i> Jessica, I'm sorry.</i>

18
00:01:11,333 --> 00:01:13,300
<i> Help us with Dad.</i>

19
00:01:16,933 --> 00:01:18,900
<i> Have some mercy on my mother!</i>

20
00:01:19,033 --> 00:01:20,333
<i> Have mercy on us!</i>

21
00:01:20,467 --> 00:01:22,533
<i> Stay with your useless family!</i>

22
00:01:22,667 --> 00:01:23,933
<i> Go to hell together!</i>

23
00:01:24,067 --> 00:01:25,267
<i> Hello?</i>

24
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:27,700
<i>Being hurt doesn't give you
the right to disrespect others.</i>

25
00:01:27,833 --> 00:01:29,267
<i> Please, for Dad's sake,</i>

26
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:31,533
<i>we don't need
negativity right now!</i>

27
00:01:31,667 --> 00:01:34,300
<i>I don't care
about your family.</i>

28
00:01:34,433 --> 00:01:35,833
<i>So that's why something
seems strange with you.</i>

29
00:01:35,967 --> 00:01:37,900
<i> Jane, my foot!</i>

30
00:01:38,033 --> 00:01:40,767
<i>- Andrea, I'm sorry.
- Don't call me your sister.</i>

31
00:01:40,933 --> 00:01:41,700
<i> You're not my sister.</i>

32
00:01:41,833 --> 00:01:43,167
<i> When did they get here?</i>

33
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:44,333
<i> When?</i>

34
00:01:44,467 --> 00:01:45,200
<i> Coleen!</i>

35
00:01:45,333 --> 00:01:46,333
<i> Last week.</i>

36
00:01:46,467 --> 00:01:48,900
<i> You really are shameless!</i>

37
00:01:49,033 --> 00:01:52,067
<i>Ate Andrea, please don't be mad
at Ate Coleen.</i>

38
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:54,600
<i> I said, stop calling me "Ate"!</i>

39
00:01:54,733 --> 00:01:55,967
<i> Stay out of this.</i>

40
00:01:56,100 --> 00:01:57,233
<i> You're not even family.</i>

41
00:01:57,367 --> 00:01:58,900
<i> Wash these dishes.</i>

42
00:02:00,433 --> 00:02:01,867
<i> Didang, here.</i>

43
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,067
<i> I'll do it.</i>

44
00:02:04,567 --> 00:02:05,767
<i> Sorry.</i>

45
00:02:07,733 --> 00:02:08,767
<i> I'm going back to the house.</i>

46
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:10,300
<i>But you and Jessica
need to leave first.</i>

47
00:02:10,433 --> 00:02:13,067
<i>Auntie Felma said we could stay.</i>

48
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,100
<i> Dad was talking to you calmly.</i>

49
00:02:15,267 --> 00:02:16,667
<i>Why can't you meet him halfway?</i>

50
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:19,367
<i>Who are you to tell me
what to do, huh?</i>

51
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:20,833
<i> Don't answer back, dear.</i>

52
00:02:20,967 --> 00:02:23,233
<i> Dad, it's just so frustrating!</i>

53
00:02:23,367 --> 00:02:27,167
<i>You've been humble and
apologetic for the longest time.</i>

54
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:29,067
<i>But she's still being
so stubborn!</i>

55
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:34,200
I'll go check on Mom.

56
00:02:34,333 --> 00:02:35,333
Auntie.

57
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:37,300
Jessica.

58
00:02:37,433 --> 00:02:38,267
Jessica!

59
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,733
Jessica, please.

60
00:02:39,867 --> 00:02:41,167
Please.

61
00:02:41,300 --> 00:02:42,567
I'm really sorry.

62
00:03:17,967 --> 00:03:20,533
Manuel's life
is in danger, Miles,

63
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:22,500
because of that scammer daughter
of his!

64
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,800
Honestly,

65
00:03:24,933 --> 00:03:26,000
that woman should be held
responsible

66
00:03:26,133 --> 00:03:27,467
for what happened to him.

67
00:03:28,533 --> 00:03:30,000
Come on, Hazel.

68
00:03:30,133 --> 00:03:32,400
Nobody wanted this to happen.

69
00:03:32,533 --> 00:03:34,333
Look, that Andrea girl

70
00:03:34,467 --> 00:03:36,567
is just a victim
of that lending company.

71
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:39,433
And her friend
or boyfriend, whatever,

72
00:03:39,567 --> 00:03:40,967
is just caught up in it.

73
00:03:41,100 --> 00:03:42,400
She's not a victim.

74
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,533
Is it my fault she's so stupid

75
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,467
and fell
for that easy money scheme?

76
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,000
I don't care about her man.

77
00:03:51,133 --> 00:03:52,933
What matters now...

78
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:55,333
is Manuel.

79
00:03:56,067 --> 00:03:57,167
Miles,

80
00:03:59,033 --> 00:04:03,267
I don't know what will happen to
me if I lose Manuel.

81
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,000
- I don't want to lose Manuel.
- No, no.

82
00:04:05,133 --> 00:04:07,233
Don't say that. Please.

83
00:04:07,367 --> 00:04:08,733
Hazel.

84
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:13,933
What are you doing here?

85
00:04:14,967 --> 00:04:16,300
Isn't it clear?

86
00:04:17,367 --> 00:04:19,967
Only the patient's family
is allowed here.

87
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:21,467
Hazel, please.

88
00:04:22,567 --> 00:04:23,567
Let's not fight.

89
00:04:24,633 --> 00:04:26,900
Manuel needs us.

90
00:04:27,033 --> 00:04:28,267
No.

91
00:04:28,433 --> 00:04:29,633
He doesn't need you all.

92
00:04:30,533 --> 00:04:34,333
And you, none of you,
have any right to my husband.

93
00:04:35,667 --> 00:04:36,967
Mom!

94
00:04:37,100 --> 00:04:38,567
Get out!

95
00:04:50,233 --> 00:04:51,133
Why are you pushing?

96
00:04:52,300 --> 00:04:53,233
Do you want me...

97
00:04:53,367 --> 00:04:54,733
to have the guard drag you out?

98
00:04:54,867 --> 00:04:56,000
Jessica, call the guard!

99
00:04:56,133 --> 00:04:56,900
Come on.

100
00:04:57,033 --> 00:04:58,367
Calm down, Hazel.

101
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:01,700
I'm sorry, Miles.
They really have some nerve.

102
00:05:01,867 --> 00:05:03,667
This is the family waiting area.

103
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:06,500
You have no right
to throw us out!

104
00:05:06,633 --> 00:05:08,267
Family waiting area.

105
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:10,567
Did you hear what you just said?

106
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:11,900
Family.

107
00:05:12,033 --> 00:05:13,433
Who's the real family here?

108
00:05:13,567 --> 00:05:14,933
Who's the real Cruz?

109
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:17,100
We're Manuel's
family, too!

110
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:18,033
No!

111
00:05:19,033 --> 00:05:20,700
Only us!

112
00:05:20,833 --> 00:05:22,633
Only Jessica and I
are his real family!

113
00:05:22,767 --> 00:05:23,967
The legal family.

114
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:25,600
And you?

115
00:05:25,733 --> 00:05:27,367
You're the
illegitimate family!

116
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:28,867
We're also his children.

117
00:05:30,267 --> 00:05:33,300
We carry his last name.
We have rights too.

118
00:05:33,433 --> 00:05:35,567
Bastard children...

119
00:05:35,733 --> 00:05:37,467
who disowned their father.

120
00:05:39,133 --> 00:05:40,767
- That's enough.
- Don't you feel guilty?

121
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:43,700
Especially you?

122
00:05:45,033 --> 00:05:48,167
Manuel's life is in danger
because of you!

123
00:05:49,133 --> 00:05:50,333
I said that's enough.

124
00:05:50,467 --> 00:05:51,167
No.

125
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:53,100
These people
are shameless!

126
00:05:54,067 --> 00:05:55,567
You hurt my daughter,

127
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:57,500
and now this happened to Manuel
because of you!

128
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,500
So,

129
00:06:00,633 --> 00:06:03,400
if Manuel survives
this operation,

130
00:06:03,533 --> 00:06:07,533
you'll never get near him again.

131
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:10,100
Even if he dies
on that operating table,

132
00:06:10,233 --> 00:06:12,533
you won't even get to see
his body.

133
00:06:12,667 --> 00:06:14,167
You're a demon!

134
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:15,733
No matter what you do,

135
00:06:15,867 --> 00:06:18,867
- you can't stop us! Demon!
- Andrea!

136
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,500
Stop!

137
00:06:20,633 --> 00:06:22,067
Wait!

138
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:24,667
We're in a hospital!
What are you doing?

139
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:26,600
There are other patients here!

140
00:06:26,733 --> 00:06:28,233
Show some respect!

141
00:06:29,667 --> 00:06:30,733
Guard!

142
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:34,267
Ma'am, Sir.
Please, that's enough.

143
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:37,700
I'm asking you nicely.

144
00:06:37,833 --> 00:06:39,333
Please step outside.

145
00:06:48,667 --> 00:06:50,367
Nurse Miles, I'm begging you.

146
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:52,533
Please don't make us leave.

147
00:06:52,667 --> 00:06:54,600
We'll stay in the hallway
if we have to.

148
00:06:55,833 --> 00:06:57,533
Please understand.

149
00:06:57,667 --> 00:06:59,000
We're in a hospital.

150
00:06:59,133 --> 00:07:01,500
We have rules here.

151
00:07:01,633 --> 00:07:04,433
We can't just ignore that.

152
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:07,467
We promise
we won't cause any trouble.

153
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:10,433
No. You've already caused
enough trouble, right?

154
00:07:10,567 --> 00:07:12,767
So I'm sorry, but I really
can't grant your request.

155
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:15,567
- Nurse Miles, I'm just asking.
- Son...

156
00:07:15,733 --> 00:07:16,767
let's not push it.

157
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,400
Can we please just
ask for a favor?

158
00:07:21,567 --> 00:07:24,500
Could you please
give us an update...

159
00:07:24,633 --> 00:07:26,267
after the operation?

160
00:07:27,367 --> 00:07:31,633
We'd like to know
how Manuel's doing.

161
00:07:31,767 --> 00:07:33,100
Ma'am, I'm really sorry.

162
00:07:33,233 --> 00:07:34,400
But patient updates

163
00:07:34,533 --> 00:07:36,900
can only be released
to immediate family members.

164
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:39,867
But don't worry, okay?

165
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:43,067
I'll talk to Hazel.

166
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:46,100
But I can't promise
you anything.

167
00:07:46,233 --> 00:07:47,667
I'm really sorry.

168
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:49,167
Please excuse us.

169
00:07:55,967 --> 00:07:57,200
That's enough.

170
00:08:01,633 --> 00:08:02,967
Sorry, Mom.

171
00:08:04,167 --> 00:08:05,533
It's my fault.

172
00:08:07,133 --> 00:08:08,533
Sorry.

173
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:13,367
What's up, sis?

174
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:14,867
Did you get rid of them?

175
00:08:16,333 --> 00:08:18,600
You know, Hazel,
what you did back there

176
00:08:18,733 --> 00:08:21,700
is so unbecoming
of a senior nurse

177
00:08:21,867 --> 00:08:25,933
of Southcrest Premiere Hospital.

178
00:08:26,067 --> 00:08:27,033
Miles,

179
00:08:28,067 --> 00:08:30,367
you know my story.

180
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:32,667
You have to understand.

181
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:35,467
I was just protecting
my rights as the legal wife.

182
00:08:36,667 --> 00:08:38,100
My daughter and I
have rights to Manuel,

183
00:08:38,233 --> 00:08:40,000
not that illegitimate family.

184
00:08:40,133 --> 00:08:44,800
Yes, you're the legal wife.
You have rights, I get it.

185
00:08:44,933 --> 00:08:47,033
But don't forget

186
00:08:47,167 --> 00:08:50,167
you're also a nurse
here at this hospital.

187
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:54,467
You represent the hospital,
even when you're not on duty.

188
00:08:54,633 --> 00:08:57,033
What should I have done?

189
00:08:57,167 --> 00:08:58,333
Entertain them?

190
00:08:58,467 --> 00:08:59,800
Assist them?

191
00:09:00,733 --> 00:09:02,967
Should I have gotten close
to them?

192
00:09:03,100 --> 00:09:04,333
No.

193
00:09:04,467 --> 00:09:06,367
You shouldn't have engaged
with them.

194
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:08,300
You should have
let me handle it!

195
00:09:11,133 --> 00:09:12,033
I'm sorry.

196
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:14,967
But they triggered me, Miles.

197
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:16,400
You saw it, right?

198
00:09:17,633 --> 00:09:18,767
They started it.

199
00:09:18,900 --> 00:09:20,400
They were the first ones
to come at me.

200
00:09:20,533 --> 00:09:22,767
Yes, but you could've
avoided it, right?

201
00:09:24,733 --> 00:09:27,200
For heaven's sake, Hazel.

202
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,933
You shouldn't let
your personal issues

203
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:32,367
get in the way
of your profession.

204
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:35,833
Not in this hospital,
not on my watch!

205
00:09:35,967 --> 00:09:37,200
Look,

206
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:39,100
please don't hold this
against me, okay?

207
00:09:39,233 --> 00:09:41,100
We're friends, I get it.

208
00:09:41,233 --> 00:09:43,667
I understand you.

209
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:45,633
But in this hospital,

210
00:09:45,767 --> 00:09:47,533
I'm your boss.

211
00:09:48,933 --> 00:09:50,900
Learn to respect that.

212
00:09:51,033 --> 00:09:52,333
Follow orders!

213
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:56,267
Let this be a warning to you.

214
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:59,067
I don't want this
to happen again, okay?

215
00:10:06,533 --> 00:10:09,700
This isn't the only entrance, we
can go through the parking area.

216
00:10:09,833 --> 00:10:12,800
Or even here, it's a different
guard on duty now anyway.

217
00:10:12,933 --> 00:10:15,333
Not the one with Nurse Miles.
The one who threw us out.

218
00:10:15,467 --> 00:10:16,867
Son...

219
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:20,133
even if we get inside, we still
won't get near your father.

220
00:10:22,533 --> 00:10:24,600
Hazel's always watching.

221
00:10:24,733 --> 00:10:26,200
No, Mom. Let's wait
until she falls asleep.

222
00:10:26,333 --> 00:10:28,133
Then we sneak in.

223
00:10:28,267 --> 00:10:30,800
Hazel works here, son.

224
00:10:30,933 --> 00:10:32,867
I'm sure she'll leave
instructions

225
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,367
with the other nurses.

226
00:10:35,367 --> 00:10:37,567
And Alice is also there,

227
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:39,533
always following her orders.

228
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:43,133
So please, let's just go home.

229
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:44,767
No, Mom. I can't.

230
00:10:45,367 --> 00:10:48,033
I won't be at peace
until I know how Dad's doing.

231
00:10:49,167 --> 00:10:51,033
Let me handle this.

232
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:55,167
I still have one more
patient anyway.

233
00:10:56,567 --> 00:10:59,533
I'll wait
until Joel comes out of the OR.

234
00:10:59,667 --> 00:11:00,800
Then...

235
00:11:01,733 --> 00:11:03,967
I'll try to get news about Dad.

236
00:11:05,167 --> 00:11:06,900
I'll call you right away.

237
00:11:08,633 --> 00:11:10,000
Thank you, dear.

238
00:11:18,267 --> 00:11:19,733
Why, Mom?

239
00:11:23,367 --> 00:11:25,100
I just missed you.

240
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:30,333
I missed you, dear.

241
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:33,667
I missed you, too.

242
00:11:35,667 --> 00:11:37,433
I miss all of you so much.

243
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:40,333
Especially Dad.

244
00:11:41,433 --> 00:11:43,167
I miss Dad so much, Mom.

245
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:55,867
Jessica, any updates?

246
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,833
Did the illegitimate family
come back?

247
00:11:59,267 --> 00:12:00,333
No, Mom.

248
00:12:01,333 --> 00:12:02,400
Good.

249
00:12:03,867 --> 00:12:07,233
Darn Felma
and her shameless kids.

250
00:12:07,367 --> 00:12:08,400
Now...

251
00:12:08,533 --> 00:12:10,333
I'm the one who got scolded.

252
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:15,500
Jessica,

253
00:12:15,667 --> 00:12:17,300
listen to me.

254
00:12:17,433 --> 00:12:19,200
You saw
what could happen, right?

255
00:12:20,133 --> 00:12:22,233
Now that they're patching
things up,

256
00:12:22,367 --> 00:12:24,600
they might team up
to take your dad away.

257
00:12:26,133 --> 00:12:27,767
You saw them.

258
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,700
They showed up in full force.

259
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:32,600
Only the youngest
who attacked you wasn't there.

260
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:34,500
But dear,

261
00:12:35,567 --> 00:12:36,967
don't let it happen.

262
00:12:37,900 --> 00:12:40,500
Don't let your dad
go back to them.

263
00:12:40,633 --> 00:12:42,500
Because if he does,

264
00:12:43,867 --> 00:12:45,667
he'll push through
with the annulment.

265
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,500
We fight, okay?

266
00:12:49,633 --> 00:12:51,067
We fight back.

267
00:12:54,267 --> 00:12:56,600
Mom, why is the surgery
taking so long?

268
00:12:56,733 --> 00:12:58,567
Still no update?

269
00:13:01,333 --> 00:13:02,767
I know.

270
00:13:02,900 --> 00:13:05,167
It's been two hours, and the OR
nurse still hasn't come out.

271
00:13:06,567 --> 00:13:09,367
She said your dad is stable.

272
00:13:10,300 --> 00:13:11,667
But as of now,

273
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:15,100
the surgery is still ongoing.

274
00:13:15,233 --> 00:13:18,367
And there's no estimated time
yet for when it'll finish.

275
00:13:26,967 --> 00:13:29,633
The wait is killing me, Mom.

276
00:13:35,267 --> 00:13:36,500
Dear,

277
00:13:36,633 --> 00:13:37,667
I know.

278
00:13:39,167 --> 00:13:40,167
I feel the same.

279
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:43,867
But for now,

280
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,333
all we can do...

281
00:13:46,467 --> 00:13:48,300
is pray for your dad.

282
00:13:49,633 --> 00:13:51,433
Don't worry.

283
00:13:51,567 --> 00:13:52,967
He's in good hands.

284
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:06,433
Mom, I'm scared
of what Hazel said.

285
00:14:07,367 --> 00:14:09,700
What if it comes true

286
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:13,133
and Dad doesn't survive
the surgery?

287
00:14:13,267 --> 00:14:14,433
Mom...

288
00:14:18,833 --> 00:14:21,733
I haven't even told him that...

289
00:14:21,867 --> 00:14:23,600
I've forgiven him.

290
00:14:25,267 --> 00:14:29,367
I haven't said sorry for all
the hurtful things I said.

291
00:14:34,633 --> 00:14:37,267
All Dad knows is I'm mad at him.

292
00:14:39,167 --> 00:14:41,100
He doesn't know...

293
00:14:41,233 --> 00:14:43,067
I still love him so, so much.

294
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:46,200
Dear...

295
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:48,833
Manuel will fight.

296
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:52,100
He'll make it through.

297
00:14:53,333 --> 00:14:54,567
And when he wakes up,

298
00:14:56,233 --> 00:14:58,067
Hazel won't be able
to stop him anymore.

299
00:14:59,533 --> 00:15:01,300
Because your dad himself...

300
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:03,767
will come to us.

301
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:31,400
Thank you, son.

302
00:15:37,133 --> 00:15:38,233
Coleen?

303
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,233
Coleen, dear?

304
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:44,000
Mom?

305
00:15:45,733 --> 00:15:46,933
Jeff.

306
00:15:49,067 --> 00:15:51,400
How's Dad?

307
00:15:56,333 --> 00:15:58,167
He was still in...

308
00:15:58,300 --> 00:16:01,133
the OR when we left
the hospital.

309
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:05,133
Why did you leave him?

310
00:16:06,333 --> 00:16:08,067
Hazel kicked us out.

311
00:16:09,167 --> 00:16:11,500
She said only she and Jessica
have the right to be with Dad.

312
00:16:12,867 --> 00:16:14,267
She's so cruel!

313
00:16:15,967 --> 00:16:17,200
And Jessica?

314
00:16:17,333 --> 00:16:19,967
She just agreed?

315
00:16:21,367 --> 00:16:23,667
Jessica couldn't really do
anything, dear.

316
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:26,900
But Mom, maybe she could've.

317
00:16:27,933 --> 00:16:30,133
She could've at least stood up
to Hazel,

318
00:16:30,267 --> 00:16:35,067
or offered to update you about
Dad, so you wouldn't worry.

319
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:36,367
Coleen, you really think
she'd do that

320
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:38,533
after what happened between
the two of you?

321
00:16:38,667 --> 00:16:41,000
Sorry, but you picked the
wrong time to fight with her.

322
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:44,700
I want to go to
the hospital.

323
00:16:46,033 --> 00:16:47,933
I want to see Dad.

324
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:51,733
If I need to apologize
to Jessica, I will.

325
00:16:51,867 --> 00:16:55,067
Even if she lashes
out at me, it's fine.

326
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:58,767
Coleen, don't. We don't stand
a chance against Hazel.

327
00:16:58,900 --> 00:17:01,433
Dad's with her,
where she works.

328
00:17:01,567 --> 00:17:03,433
She gets to act
like a queen there.

329
00:17:04,733 --> 00:17:06,600
So what, we just give up?

330
00:17:07,833 --> 00:17:08,800
No, sweetie.

331
00:17:10,167 --> 00:17:12,867
Let's get through
the night first.

332
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,433
Let's pray that...

333
00:17:15,967 --> 00:17:17,867
the surgery is a success.

334
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:20,767
Then, when he wakes up,

335
00:17:20,900 --> 00:17:22,300
we'll go see him.

336
00:17:29,267 --> 00:17:30,767
That's enough.

337
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:32,800
We won't let Hazel...

338
00:17:33,867 --> 00:17:36,233
get her way.

339
00:17:36,367 --> 00:17:38,667
You will see your dad.

340
00:17:40,733 --> 00:17:42,133
Especially now...

341
00:17:43,767 --> 00:17:47,200
that Andrea wants...

342
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:49,433
to make things right with him.

343
00:18:11,933 --> 00:18:14,667
Is Dad's surgery almost done,
Mom?

344
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,900
It should be, dear.

345
00:18:17,033 --> 00:18:20,033
I hope so.
It's been over five hours.

346
00:18:23,833 --> 00:18:25,500
Hey.

347
00:18:25,633 --> 00:18:28,267
What are you still doing here?
Why are you still here?

348
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:30,200
Want me to call the cops?

349
00:18:30,333 --> 00:18:32,733
Don't be so assuming, Hazel.

350
00:18:32,867 --> 00:18:34,600
I didn't come here for Dad.

351
00:18:34,733 --> 00:18:36,067
I have another patient.

352
00:18:37,433 --> 00:18:38,500
Oh, right.

353
00:18:38,633 --> 00:18:40,600
Your dad's not your only victim.

354
00:18:40,733 --> 00:18:43,300
Even your boyfriend,
who got stabbed.

355
00:18:43,433 --> 00:18:44,767
Poor guy.

356
00:18:53,367 --> 00:18:54,400
Joel?

357
00:18:54,533 --> 00:18:55,667
Hey, how are you feeling?

358
00:18:55,833 --> 00:18:57,133
How's the pain?

359
00:18:57,267 --> 00:18:58,733
He's out of the woods.

360
00:18:58,867 --> 00:19:01,467
Good thing the wound
didn't hit deep into his liver.

361
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:06,200
But he'll need to stay a few
more days to recover properly.

362
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:08,133
Okay. Thank you.

363
00:19:28,567 --> 00:19:30,167
Coleen, sit down for a bit.

364
00:19:42,100 --> 00:19:44,000
Mom's trying to stay strong.

365
00:19:45,867 --> 00:19:47,300
But I can tell...

366
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:51,867
she's hiding her fear and worry.

367
00:19:53,733 --> 00:19:55,133
I noticed, too.

368
00:19:57,367 --> 00:20:00,133
Our family's going through
so much.

369
00:20:00,267 --> 00:20:01,567
I know.

370
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:03,567
Feels like
we're living in a drama series

371
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:06,933
with everything happening.

372
00:20:08,967 --> 00:20:09,867
But even with all the problems,

373
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,933
at least something
good came out of it.

374
00:20:12,067 --> 00:20:13,933
Look at Mom and Andrea.
They're okay now.

375
00:20:15,067 --> 00:20:16,267
I hope...

376
00:20:17,933 --> 00:20:19,767
I hope our family
becomes whole again.

377
00:20:20,667 --> 00:20:22,067
I hope so, too, Jeff.

378
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:30,433
Has Andrea called yet?

379
00:20:30,567 --> 00:20:33,667
Maybe she has news
about your dad.

380
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:35,700
Not yet, Mom.

381
00:20:36,667 --> 00:20:38,967
Jeff, please call Andrea.

382
00:20:46,067 --> 00:20:47,600
Sonny's been detained.

383
00:20:49,633 --> 00:20:51,400
- Take it easy.
- Sorry.

384
00:20:53,767 --> 00:20:56,900
Atty. Yeban is already handling
the case for him.

385
00:21:01,933 --> 00:21:03,100
Sorry.

386
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:07,433
Hello, Jeff.

387
00:21:07,567 --> 00:21:09,300
Andrea?

388
00:21:09,467 --> 00:21:11,167
Any news about Dad?

389
00:21:11,300 --> 00:21:13,133
None yet.

390
00:21:13,267 --> 00:21:16,600
It's like Hazel's the warden,
standing guard outside the OR.

391
00:21:16,733 --> 00:21:17,967
How's Joel?

392
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:20,533
Here...

393
00:21:20,667 --> 00:21:22,367
he's awake now.

394
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:25,600
He just came out
of the recovery room.

395
00:21:25,733 --> 00:21:27,867
Thank God. That's a relief.

396
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:30,067
Tell him to get well soon, okay?

397
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:32,567
I'll visit
once I get the chance.

398
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:34,000
<i> Andrea, dear.</i>

399
00:21:34,933 --> 00:21:36,733
Take care of him, okay?

400
00:21:36,867 --> 00:21:38,533
Yes, Mom.

401
00:21:38,667 --> 00:21:40,067
I won't leave him.

402
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,433
I owe him my life.

403
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:46,167
But sis,

404
00:21:46,300 --> 00:21:49,167
please still find out
about Dad's condition, okay?

405
00:21:49,300 --> 00:21:51,500
<i>We can't sleep,
thinking about it.</i>

406
00:21:51,633 --> 00:21:52,733
Okay, sweetie.

407
00:21:52,867 --> 00:21:53,833
I'll handle it.

408
00:21:55,067 --> 00:21:57,167
Go ahead, Andrea.
Take care of Joel.

409
00:22:10,733 --> 00:22:12,100
Sorry, Joel.

410
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:18,000
Sorry that you're in danger
because of me.

411
00:22:23,367 --> 00:22:24,800
I've messed up your life.

412
00:22:26,700 --> 00:22:28,567
Since we met,

413
00:22:31,633 --> 00:22:33,867
you've been dragged
into all my problems.

414
00:22:37,867 --> 00:22:40,167
You've always been the one
helping me.

415
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:42,433
Supporting,

416
00:22:42,567 --> 00:22:43,967
taking care of me.

417
00:22:47,633 --> 00:22:48,800
Now it's my turn.

418
00:22:51,733 --> 00:22:52,967
Thank you.

419
00:22:55,933 --> 00:22:57,467
Not because...

420
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,000
you saved me.

421
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:03,200
Thank you for being my friend.

422
00:23:05,067 --> 00:23:07,800
Thank you
for being my best friend.

423
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,833
Dear God.

424
00:23:47,967 --> 00:23:49,500
Dear God.

425
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:54,633
Dear God,
please don't take Manuel.

426
00:23:55,667 --> 00:23:57,100
Not now.

427
00:23:59,167 --> 00:24:01,033
Not yet.

428
00:24:03,067 --> 00:24:05,033
Please save him.

429
00:24:05,167 --> 00:24:07,300
<i> Are you pregnant? Yes!</i>

430
00:24:08,367 --> 00:24:09,767
<i> We're going to have a baby!</i>

431
00:24:09,900 --> 00:24:12,533
If he goes back to Hazel,

432
00:24:12,667 --> 00:24:14,833
I'll accept that.

433
00:24:16,867 --> 00:24:18,767
As long as you save him.

434
00:24:20,900 --> 00:24:24,067
But if you must take a life,

435
00:24:25,700 --> 00:24:27,400
Lord...

436
00:24:27,533 --> 00:24:29,300
take mine.

437
00:24:31,133 --> 00:24:33,433
Take mine, Lord.

438
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:37,533
Don't take Manuel's.

439
00:24:37,667 --> 00:24:42,733
I've been with our children
for a long time now.

440
00:24:42,867 --> 00:24:45,133
What I want is...

441
00:24:45,267 --> 00:24:47,033
for Manuel...

442
00:24:47,167 --> 00:24:52,300
to experience being loved

443
00:24:52,433 --> 00:24:55,600
and cared for by Jeffrey,

444
00:24:55,733 --> 00:24:57,367
Andrea,

445
00:24:57,500 --> 00:24:59,300
and Coleen.

446
00:24:59,433 --> 00:25:01,267
Lord.

447
00:25:02,333 --> 00:25:04,133
Lord.

448
00:25:07,333 --> 00:25:10,067
Please save him.

449
00:25:12,667 --> 00:25:15,567
Save Manuel.

450
00:25:24,033 --> 00:25:26,967
Dear God...

451
00:25:29,200 --> 00:25:31,800
Save Manuel.

452
00:25:43,267 --> 00:25:46,600
There are so many machines
attached to Dad.

453
00:25:46,733 --> 00:25:47,633
Is he safe?

454
00:25:47,767 --> 00:25:49,000
I don't know.

455
00:25:49,133 --> 00:25:51,000
Darn it! Do we really have
to sneak around

456
00:25:51,133 --> 00:25:53,067
just to know how Dad's doing?

457
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:53,967
Get out of there!

458
00:25:54,100 --> 00:25:54,833
Andrea!

459
00:25:54,967 --> 00:25:56,467
Let me go!

460
00:25:56,600 --> 00:25:59,233
Since Manuel signed
our marriage certificate,

461
00:25:59,367 --> 00:26:01,100
you lost your rights to him.

462
00:26:01,233 --> 00:26:03,433
We won't lose our rights
to our father.

463
00:26:03,567 --> 00:26:05,067
That's not going to happen.

464
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,467
Andrea!

465
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:09,400
I won't sue,

466
00:26:09,567 --> 00:26:13,967
but let me and my kids
be near Manuel.
